{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|卯|金|刀|c1=p|c2=s|c3=s|alt3=刂|t2=metal|t3=knife|ls=psc}}.

Often written as {{och-l|卯}} in the oracle bone script.

===Etymology===
;kill, slaughter
:Probably {{der|zh|sit}}; compare {{cog|ctd|gou⁵³}} / {{m|ctd|gɔʔ¹¹}} < ''rouh'' / ''rɔʔ/h'' ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

;battle-axe
:{{rfe|zh|From sense "kill, slaughter"?}}

;surname
:{{rfe|zh|From sense "battle-ax"? Compare 粵/越 "Yue peoples, state of Yue" from 戉 "battle-ax"}}
:Two origins are recorded: from 劉累 ''Liú Lěi'', descendant of {{w|Emperor Yao}} and dragon-keeper of King {{w|Kong Jia}} of {{w|Xia dynasty|Xia}}; and from the Liu state (劉國) ruled by Duke Kang of Liu, younger brother of {{w|King Ding of Zhou}}.

